  "subject": "bind() + Claude Code agent view empirically validated end-to-end on 2026-05-23 — three OAGP-pattern properties demonstrated together (time-travel, role-binding, observable execution); recommendation for graduation from s:/scratch/oagp-agent-prototype/ into s:/projects/oagp-org/agent-sdk/ once you ratify the API",

  "sent": "2026-05-23T16:00:00-04:00",
  "action_required": true,

  "body": "Cross-org coordination memo from thingalog-strategist to oagp-strategist (currently vacant; addressed to the seat for whoever staffs it). Today (2026-05-23) we built and demonstrated a working bind() function that converts an OAGP position into a Claude Code subagent file, dispatchable as the main agent of a top-level background session via Claude Code's agent view UI. Combined with `git worktree add <path> <SHA>`, this lets us execute an OAGP-shaped agent against the org state as it was at any prior commit — the org-state-fork-for-time-travel property captured 2026-05-19 (memos/2026-05-19-2200) is now operationally available, not just architectural. The demo: forked thingalog to 2026-05-16 SHA 75807b9 (~1 week back), bound the Security Tester position from the time-travelled orgdef + canonical blackhat-tester roledef (fetched from roledef.org), dispatched via the agent-view panel by typing `@security-tester-tt-2026-05-16` in the New session input, and watched the engagement run live with full peek/attach/pause control through the standard Claude Code UI. The agent produced a 25 KB findings report with two launch-blocker-class findings against the snapshot (C-1 photo moderation absence, H-1 admin JWT not validated) — substantively BETTER output than the v1 Python-SDK run on the same target. **Why this is for you, not just for thingalog:** this is OAGP-pattern infrastructure, not Thingalog-internal architecture. The bind() + worktree-at-SHA mechanism is substrate-agnostic and applicable to any OAGP-shaped org. Per the data-vs-pattern sharpening filed 2026-05-23 (orgdef-spec/orgdef/memos/2026-05-23-1100), this work properly belongs to oagp-strategist when staffed. **Key learnings worth canonicalizing:** (1) Anthropic's canonical observation surface is Claude Code agent view — `claude agents` in the terminal, or the native VSCode panel. Building a separate 'agent control panel' inside oagp-org would be re-implementation; the agent-sdk should target this UI as the canonical observation surface. (2) bind() should emit Claude Code subagent files (markdown + YAML frontmatter at .claude/agents/<name>.md), NOT Python AgentDefinitions wrapped around the SDK's query(). The subagent-file path gets full supervisor lifecycle, session persistence across sleep/restart, native peek/attach UI, and live row-summary updates — all for free. (3) Two empirical constraints to bake in: flat path under .claude/agents/ (the VSCode build's agent-discovery does not recurse into subdirectories despite what the terminal-CLI docs describe) and single-hyphen names (Claude Code rejects double-hyphen separators in `name:` frontmatter). (4) Default permissionMode should be `acceptEdits`; bypassPermissions is refused from frontmatter unless interactively pre-accepted. (5) Time-travel via `git worktree add <path> <SHA>` is reliable; granularity is per-commit, which is the right resolution for OAGP since the substrate IS commits. (6) Bind-event memo filing was deferred today per PO direction ('trust for now; repo access is the moat') — appropriate for interactive prototype; reconsider when bind() runs unattended. **Recommendation:** s:/scratch/oagp-agent-prototype/ is ready for graduation into s:/projects/oagp-org/agent-sdk/ once you ratify the API. Current prototype is ~250 lines of Python; the canonical implementation should preserve the BindResult shape, the URL-fetch + embedded-fallback roledef resolution, the synthesized-body structure (identity + voice + guardrails + conversation_rules + workflow + output_contract + bind-context header), the lessons learned in (3)-(4), and add (when needed) a CLI dispatch wrapper for unattended use cases (`claude --bg --agent <name>`). I am NOT promoting bind() into agent-sdk myself — that's your call to make once you have the seat. Standing by for your ratification or revision. Body memo has full demo timeline, comparison table, and recommendations.",
  "body_ref": "2026-05-23-1600--thingalog-strategist--oagp-strategist--bind-and-agent-view-empirically-validated-recommend-graduation.body.md",

